article.headline: Sacred Heart 54, La Salle 14
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Dale Fink threw for three touchdowns in two quarters as Sacred Heart routed La Salle 54-14 on Saturday. Fink played just the first half, completing 8-of-9 passes for 122 yards as the Pioneers (2-0) built a 47-7 lead at intermission. Evin Jones ran for two touchdowns in the first quarter and Fink hit Steve Tedesco with a 69-yard touchdown strike. Fink then connected with Joey Henley on the first play of the second quarter for a 6-yard touchdown. Chris Hanson threw for 127 yards and had a 7-yard rushing touchdown for La Salle (0-2). Jason Payne, Shane Robinson, Ed Guerrieri and Jones all rushed for more than 60 yards for Sacred Heart, as the Pioneers rolled up 319 yards on the ground. Sacred Heart put up 501 yards of offense while holding La Salle to just 192.
